				<DIV></DIV>I agree personal responsibility is&nbsp;the biggest factor in the blog Smed was writing about. I do disagree with Smed that MMORPG's are not designed to be addicting.&nbsp; The shear amount of time required to advance in MMORPG's, the promise of better loot, and the fact that you never really win the game makes it ripe for addiction. I remember playing Super Mario Bros for weeks unitl I finally beat the game&nbsp; but you never really do that with a MMORPG. This fact does not override personal responsibility though because with out that anything can become addicting.
				
